ARCHITECTURE CONSTRAINTS (do not violate these):

### Core Structural Decisions
1. Zero dependencies — no npm, no bundler, no framework. All files shipped as-is.
2. CSS custom properties as single source of truth — all colours, spacing, timing in `--custom-properties`. Never hard-coded in component CSS.
3. clock.css is self-contained — only stylesheet on clock page. Never borrows from other sheets.
4. rAF loops with visibilitychange pause — both clock.js and favicon-animator.js use requestAnimationFrame, never setInterval. Both pause when tab hidden.
5. Pre-allocated output buffers — no per-frame heap allocations. Five buffers (_bufOut, _bufFrom, _bufTo, _bufTime, _bufInterp) mutated in place.
6. Float64Array angle cache — apply() only writes DOM if angle has changed.
7. GPU compositor via will-change + contain — will-change: transform on .hand, contain: layout style paint on .mc.
8. localStorage-only settings persistence — keys: clk_mode, clk_hours, clk_countdown_time, clk_countdown_end. clock.js reads on load and on storage event.

### What We Never Do
- setInterval for animation → always requestAnimationFrame
- Let rAF run when tab hidden → visibilitychange pauses both loops
- Animate width/height/top/left → transform and opacity only
- Hard-code colour or spacing values → CSS custom properties from colors.css
- max-width breakpoints → mobile-first min-width only
- Inline styles in HTML → no style attribute ever
- !important in CSS → specificity-correct rule ordering
- Per-frame heap allocations in rAF loop → pre-allocated buffers
- Write DOM if angle unchanged → _lastAngles cache comparison first
- Raw localStorage values in JS logic → always sanitise/validate before use

### Hard Rules (no exceptions)
- FL-08: No inline styles anywhere
- FL-09: No max-width layout breakpoints
- FL-10: No !important (exception: prefers-reduced-motion blocks only)

